<Link id="l00316" /><CodeLine lineNumber="316"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// ASan, HWASan and Memtag sanitizers have some instrumentation that applies</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00317" /><CodeLine lineNumber="317"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// specifically to global variables.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00318" /><CodeLine lineNumber="318" lineLink="/docs/api/structs/llvm/globalvalue/sanitizermetadata"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">struct </Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/globalvalue/sanitizermetadata/#ac9ed467b801e291e5873caed022b1858">SanitizerMetadata</a> &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00319" /><CodeLine lineNumber="319" lineLink="/docs/api/structs/llvm/globalvalue/sanitizermetadata/#ac9ed467b801e291e5873caed022b1858"><Highlight kind="normal">    <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/globalvalue/sanitizermetadata/#ac9ed467b801e291e5873caed022b1858">SanitizerMetadata</a>()</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00320" /><CodeLine lineNumber="320"><Highlight kind="normal">        : <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/globalvalue/sanitizermetadata/#af14cbae5c1ca7ff03eaa9c66d41e0940">NoAddress</a>(<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/false">false</a>), <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/globalvalue/sanitizermetadata/#a3c6f90fc4359e4c8cc2ad7333254f3c7">NoHWAddress</a>(<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/false">false</a>),</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00321" /><CodeLine lineNumber="321"><Highlight kind="normal">          <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/globalvalue/sanitizermetadata/#a06dd653fcfff7260ea2ab89cc39029cb">Memtag</a>(<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/false">false</a>), <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/globalvalue/sanitizermetadata/#ac1da5875b7fe84a87d30ef1a90524c1c">IsDynInit</a>(<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/false">false</a>) &#123;&#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00322" /><CodeLine lineNumber="322"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// For ASan and HWASan, this instrumentation is implicitly applied to all</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00323" /><CodeLine lineNumber="323"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// global variables when built with -fsanitize=&#42;. What we need is a way to</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00324" /><CodeLine lineNumber="324"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// persist the information that a certain global variable should &#42;not&#42; have</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00325" /><CodeLine lineNumber="325"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// sanitizers applied, which occurs if:</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00326" /><CodeLine lineNumber="326"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   1 The global variable is in the sanitizer ignore list, or</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00327" /><CodeLine lineNumber="327"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   2 The global variable is created by the sanitizers itself for internal</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00328" /><CodeLine lineNumber="328"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//      usage, or</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00329" /><CodeLine lineNumber="329"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   3 The global variable has &#95;&#95;attribute&#95;&#95;((no&#95;sanitize(&quot;...&quot;))) or</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00330" /><CodeLine lineNumber="330"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//      &#95;&#95;attribute&#95;&#95;((disable&#95;sanitizer&#95;instrumentation)).</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00331" /><CodeLine lineNumber="331"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00332" /><CodeLine lineNumber="332"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// This is important, a some IR passes like GlobalMerge can delete global</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00333" /><CodeLine lineNumber="333"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// variables and replace them with new ones. If the old variables were</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00334" /><CodeLine lineNumber="334"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// marked to be unsanitized, then the new ones should also be.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00464" /><CodeLine lineNumber="464"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00465" /><CodeLine lineNumber="465"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Return true if the currently visible definition of this global (if any) is</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00466" /><CodeLine lineNumber="466"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// exactly the definition we will see at runtime.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00467" /><CodeLine lineNumber="467"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00468" /><CodeLine lineNumber="468"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Non-exact linkage types inhibits most non-inlining IPO, since a</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00469" /><CodeLine lineNumber="469"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// differently optimized variant of the same function can have different</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00470" /><CodeLine lineNumber="470"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// observable or undefined behavior than in the variant currently visible.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00471" /><CodeLine lineNumber="471"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// For instance, we could have started with</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00472" /><CodeLine lineNumber="472"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00473" /><CodeLine lineNumber="473"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   void foo(int &#42;v) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00474" /><CodeLine lineNumber="474"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///     int t = 5 / v&#91;0&#93;;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00475" /><CodeLine lineNumber="475"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///     (void) t;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00476" /><CodeLine lineNumber="476"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00477" /><CodeLine lineNumber="477"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00478" /><CodeLine lineNumber="478"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// and &quot;refined&quot; it to</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00479" /><CodeLine lineNumber="479"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00480" /><CodeLine lineNumber="480"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   void foo(int &#42;v) &#123; &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00481" /><CodeLine lineNumber="481"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00482" /><CodeLine lineNumber="482"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// However, we cannot infer readnone for &#96;foo&#96;, since that would justify</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00483" /><CodeLine lineNumber="483"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// DSE&#39;ing a store to &#96;v&#91;0&#93;&#96; across a call to &#96;foo&#96;, which can cause</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00484" /><CodeLine lineNumber="484"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// undefined behavior if the linker replaces the actual call destination with</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00485" /><CodeLine lineNumber="485"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// the unoptimized &#96;foo&#96;.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00486" /><CodeLine lineNumber="486"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00487" /><CodeLine lineNumber="487"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Inlining is okay across non-exact linkage types as long as they&#39;re not</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00488" /><CodeLine lineNumber="488"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// interposable (see \\c isInterposable), since in such cases the currently</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00489" /><CodeLine lineNumber="489"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// visible variant is &#42;a&#42; correct implementation of the original source</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00490" /><CodeLine lineNumber="490"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// function; it just isn&#39;t the &#42;only&#42; correct implementation.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00491" /><CodeLine lineNumber="491" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/globalvalue/#a008adb117253c7a0dde2f796be489d65"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">bool</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/globalvalue/#a008adb117253c7a0dde2f796be489d65">isDefinitionExact</a>()</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword"> const </Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">&#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00492" /><CodeLine lineNumber="492"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">return</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> !mayBeDerefined();</Highlight></CodeLine>
